# =============================================================================
# Stokowski — example .env
# =============================================================================
#
# Copy to `.env` in the directory you'll invoke `stokowski` from. The CLI
# loads `.env` from cwd before anything else; values below override shell
# env vars.
#
# Only STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH is Stokowski-interpreted. Other entries here
# (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, LINEAR_API_KEY, …) are examples of variables your
# workflow.yaml may reference via `$VAR` or pass through to agent
# subprocesses via `docker.extra_env`.
# =============================================================================

# ── Workflow discovery (bare `stokowski` CLI) ───────────────────────────────
#
# STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH accepts the same shapes as a single positional arg:
#   - A file                → `STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=workflow.yaml`
#   - A directory           → `STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=workflows/`
#   - A glob                → `STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=workflow.*.yml`
#
# Precedence: CLI args > STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH > auto-detect (./workflow.yaml,
# ./workflow.yml, ./WORKFLOW.md, in that order). Unset or empty values fall
# through to auto-detect.
#
# Examples:
#   STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=workflow.yaml
#   STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=examples/multi-project/
#   STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=workflows/workflow.*.yml
# STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=examples/multi-project/

# ── Workflow discovery (docker compose) ─────────────────────────────────────
#
# When running `docker compose up`, the orchestrator INSIDE the container
# reads STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_PATH=/app/workflow (hard-wired in docker-compose.yml).
# The HOST side of that bind mount is controlled here.
#
# STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_HOST_PATH accepts a file or a directory; the mount target
# /app/workflow adapts to whichever shape the host path is:
#
#   - A single file         → STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_HOST_PATH=./workflow.yaml    (default)
#   - A directory           → STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_HOST_PATH=./workflows/
#
# Unset → compose falls back to ./workflow.yaml (backward-compatible).
# STOKOWSKI_WORKFLOW_HOST_PATH=./workflows/

# ── Credentials referenced from workflow.yaml via $VAR ──────────────────────
# LINEAR_API_KEY=lin_api_your_key_here
# ALPHA_LINEAR_API_KEY=lin_api_alpha_team_key
# BETA_LINEAR_API_KEY=lin_api_beta_team_key

# ── Credentials passed to Docker-mode agent containers ──────────────────────
# Required for Claude Code inside containers (choose one):
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=your_generated_token_here

# Optional: GitHub token for agents that push PRs
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_...
